        "timestamp": "2019-02-21 21:09:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nDo we want to implement retry logic within music? Or push that to the client?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "ecba665782ba4efedb683e6c4459ecb2b6afcce0",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4904,
          "name": "Mohammad Salehe",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "salehe@cs.toronto.edu",
          "username": "salehe"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-22 22:06:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n> \n> Do we want to implement retry logic within music? Or push that to the client?\n\nI actually think atomicPut is a client of Music and not part of Music itself (there is no mention of atomicPut in the protocol in the paper).\n\nIn fact, retrying atomicPut itself is not a good idea in case of failure, because the acquireLock and criticalPut phases might have completed successfully and only the releaseLock phase should be retried.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
